# Plan: Add `@ai-sdk/pixelart` Provider

## Context

The Vercel AI SDK uses a layered provider architecture where each AI service is wrapped in its own `packages/<name>` package implementing the relevant `V3` model interfaces from `@ai-sdk/provider`. The task is to add a new fictional **PixelArt** image provider that:
- Only supports image generation (`ImageModelV3`) — no text, embeddings, speech, etc.
- Exports a `createPixelArt` factory function and a `pixelArt` default instance
- Accepts provider-specific options: `style` (`'pixel' | 'retro' | '8bit'`) and `pixelDensity` (number)
- Uses base URL `https://api.pixelart.ai/v1`
- Follows the exact same package structure as `packages/fal`

## Key Reference Files (read-only, do not modify)

- `packages/fal/src/fal-image-model.ts` — Image model class pattern
- `packages/fal/src/fal-provider.ts` — Factory function pattern
- `packages/fal/src/fal-image-settings.ts` — Model ID type pattern
- `packages/fal/src/fal-image-options.ts` — Provider options + zod schema pattern
- `packages/fal/src/version.ts` — VERSION constant pattern
- `packages/fal/src/index.ts` — Re-export pattern
- `packages/fal/package.json` — Package.json structure
- `packages/fal/tsconfig.json` / `tsconfig.build.json` / `tsup.config.ts` — Build config
- `packages/fal/turbo.json` / `vitest.*.config.js` — Test/turbo configs

## Utilities to Reuse (from `@ai-sdk/provider-utils`)

- `postJsonToApi` — HTTP POST with JSON body
- `getFromApi` + `createBinaryResponseHandler` — Download image bytes from URL
- `createJsonResponseHandler` — Parse successful JSON responses
- `createJsonErrorResponseHandler` — Parse error responses
- `createStatusCodeErrorResponseHandler` — Status-code-based error handler
- `combineHeaders` — Merge header objects
- `resolve` — Resolve a `Resolvable<T>` (sync or async headers)
- `withoutTrailingSlash` — Normalize base URL
- `withUserAgentSuffix` — Add SDK user-agent suffix to headers
- `loadApiKey` — Load API key from options or env variable
- `parseProviderOptions` — Validate & parse provider-specific options with zod
- `InferSchema`, `lazySchema`, `zodSchema` — Schema type utilities

## Files to Create

### 1. `packages/pixelart/package.json`

```json
{
  "name": "@ai-sdk/pixelart",
  "version": "0.0.0",
  "license": "Apache-2.0",
  "sideEffects": false,
  "main": "./dist/index.js",
  "module": "./dist/index.mjs",
  "types": "./dist/index.d.ts",
  "files": [
    "dist/**/*",
    "src",
    "!src/**/*.test.ts",
    "!src/**/*.test-d.ts",
    "!src/**/__snapshots__",
    "!src/**/__fixtures__",
    "CHANGELOG.md",
    "README.md"
  ],
  "scripts": {
    "build": "pnpm clean && tsup --tsconfig tsconfig.build.json",
    "build:watch": "pnpm clean && tsup --watch",
    "clean": "del-cli dist *.tsbuildinfo",
    "type-check": "tsc --build",
    "test": "pnpm test:node && pnpm test:edge",
    "test:update": "pnpm test:node -u",
    "test:watch": "vitest --config vitest.node.config.js",
    "test:edge": "vitest --config vitest.edge.config.js --run",
    "test:node": "vitest --config vitest.node.config.js --run"
  },
  "exports": {
    "./package.json": "./package.json",
    ".": {
      "types": "./dist/index.d.ts",
      "import": "./dist/index.mjs",
      "require": "./dist/index.js"
    }
  },
